{"title":"Microsoft shares its process (and discarded ideas) for redone Windows 11 Start menu","link":"https://arstechnica.com/gadgets/2025/05/microsoft-shares-its-process-and-discarded-ideas-for-redone-windows-11-start-menu/","date":1747169074000,"content":"<p>Microsoft put a lot of focus on Windows 11's design when it <a href=\"https://arstechnica.com/gadgets/2021/10/windows-11-the-ars-technica-review/\">released the operating system in 2021</a>, making a clean break with the design language of Windows 10 (which had, itself, simply tweaked and adapted Windows 8's design language from 2012). Since then, Microsoft has continued to modify the software's design in bits and pieces, both for <a href=\"https://arstechnica.com/gadgets/2021/10/the-latest-app-to-get-a-windows-11-redesign-the-humble-notepad/\">individual apps</a> and for <a href=\"https://arstechnica.com/gadgets/2022/07/the-windows-11-taskbar-is-getting-better-for-people-who-open-tons-of-apps/\">foundational UI elements</a> like the Taskbar, system tray, and Windows Explorer.</p>\n<p>Microsoft is currently testing <a href=\"https://arstechnica.com/gadgets/2025/04/back-to-basics-microsoft-tests-overhauled-start-menu-in-windows-11-beta-builds/\">a redesigned version of the Windows 11 Start menu</a>, one that reuses most of the familiar elements from the current design but reorganizes them and gives users a few additional customization options. On its Microsoft Design blog today, the company <a href=\"https://microsoft.design/articles/start-fresh-redesigning-windows-start-menu/\">walked through the new design</a> and showed some of the ideas that were tried and discarded in the process.</p>\n<figure>\n      <img width=\"1024\" height=\"576\" src=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/exploration3-1024x576.jpeg\" alt=\"\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/exploration3-1024x576.jpeg 1024w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/exploration3-640x360.jpeg 640w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/exploration3-768x432.jpeg 768w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/exploration3-1536x864.jpeg 1536w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/exploration3-384x216.jpeg 384w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/exploration3-1152x648.jpeg 1152w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/exploration3-980x551.jpeg 980w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/exploration3-1440x810.jpeg 1440w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/exploration3.jpeg 1921w\" />\n      <figcaption>\n        <div>\n    <div></div>\n    <div>\n      This discarded Start menu design toyed with an almost Windows XP-ish left-hand sidebar, among other elements.\n\n              <span>\n          Credit:\n\n          \n          Microsoft\n\n                  </span>\n          </div>\n  </div>\n      </figcaption>\n    </figure>\n      <figure>\n      <img width=\"1024\" height=\"576\" src=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/exploration5-1024x576.jpeg\" alt=\"\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/exploration5-1024x576.jpeg 1024w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/exploration5-640x360.jpeg 640w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/exploration5-768x432.jpeg 768w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/exploration5-1536x864.jpeg 1536w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/exploration5-384x216.jpeg 384w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/exploration5-1152x648.jpeg 1152w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/exploration5-980x551.jpeg 980w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/exploration5-1440x810.jpeg 1440w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/exploration5.jpeg 1920w\" />\n      <figcaption>\n        <div>\n    <div></div>\n    <div>\n      Some designs brings to mind the full-screen Start experience of Windows 8.\n\n              <span>\n          Credit:\n\n          \n          Microsoft\n\n                  </span>\n          </div>\n  </div>\n      </figcaption>\n    </figure>\n      <figure>\n      <img width=\"1024\" height=\"576\" src=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/exploration1-1024x576.jpeg\" alt=\"\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/exploration1-1024x576.jpeg 1024w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/exploration1-640x360.jpeg 640w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/exploration1-768x432.jpeg 768w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/exploration1-1536x864.jpeg 1536w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/exploration1-384x216.jpeg 384w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/exploration1-1152x648.jpeg 1152w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/exploration1-980x551.jpeg 980w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/exploration1-1440x810.jpeg 1440w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/exploration1.jpeg 1921w\" />\n      <figcaption>\n        <div>\n    <div></div>\n    <div>\n      Another big design with acres of icons and more space dedicated to non-app-icons.\n\n              <span>\n          Credit:\n\n          \n          Microsoft\n\n                  </span>\n          </div>\n  </div>\n      </figcaption>\n    </figure>\n      <figure>\n      <img width=\"1024\" height=\"576\" src=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/exploration4-1024x576.jpeg\" alt=\"\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/exploration4-1024x576.jpeg 1024w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/exploration4-640x360.jpeg 640w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/exploration4-768x432.jpeg 768w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/exploration4-1536x864.jpeg 1536w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/exploration4-384x216.jpeg 384w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/exploration4-1152x648.jpeg 1152w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/exploration4-980x551.jpeg 980w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/exploration4-1440x810.jpeg 1440w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/exploration4.jpeg 1921w\" />\n      <figcaption>\n        <div>\n    <div></div>\n    <div>\n      This design included thumbnail previews for recently opened files.\n\n              <span>\n          Credit:\n\n          \n          Microsoft\n\n                  </span>\n          </div>\n  </div>\n      </figcaption>\n    </figure>\n      <figure>\n      <img width=\"1024\" height=\"576\" src=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/exploration2-1024x576.jpeg\" alt=\"\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/exploration2-1024x576.jpeg 1024w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/exploration2-640x360.jpeg 640w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/exploration2-768x432.jpeg 768w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/exploration2-1536x864.jpeg 1536w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/exploration2-384x216.jpeg 384w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/exploration2-1152x648.jpeg 1152w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/exploration2-980x551.jpeg 980w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/exploration2-1440x810.jpeg 1440w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/exploration2.jpeg 1921w\" />\n      <figcaption>\n        <div>\n    <div></div>\n    <div>\n      Another discarded Start menu design.\n\n              <span>\n          Credit:\n\n          \n          Microsoft\n\n                  </span>\n          </div>\n  </div>\n      </figcaption>\n    </figure>\n  \n<p>Microsoft says it tested its menu designs with \"over 300 Windows 11 fans\" in unmoderated studies, \"and dozens more\" in \"live co-creation calls.\" These testers' behavior and reactions informed what Microsoft kept and what it discarded.</p><p><a href=\"https://arstechnica.com/gadgets/2025/05/microsoft-shares-its-process-and-discarded-ideas-for-redone-windows-11-start-menu/\">Read full article</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://arstechnica.com/gadgets/2025/05/microsoft-shares-its-process-and-discarded-ideas-for-redone-windows-11-start-menu/#comments\">Comments</a></p>","author":"Andrew Cunningham","siteTitle":"Ars Technica","siteHash":"5b0ddf6e8923e49262a7894cfd77962733e43fbcc565a103b48373820b310636","entryHash":"a247929fd1db84f67091e7050b413e47ffaaa1011299c7f93bc2be7e7c5ea82c","category":"Tech"}